In article <0#6nw8k.nagle@netcom.com> nagle@netcom.com (John Nagle) writes:
>     Another alternative is to package smart cards as things one puts
>on keyrings, rather than in wallets.  Such devices have been
>built, but don't sell well.

Crypto Ignition Keys (CIKs) for STU-III secure phones are like this.
They resemble a child's play key (plastic and oversized) but with
electrical contacts between each tooth. The key is actually a carrier
for a nonvolatile memory.

Phil
